🛰 Space Fact of the Day – Cold Gas Thrusters

Cold Gas Thrusters are one of the simplest and safest propulsion systems used in **small satellites and CubeSats**.

They work by **expelling compressed inert gas (like nitrogen)** through a nozzle to generate thrust.

Why They’re Useful

* Perfect for **small attitude adjustments**
* Clean and safe operation
* Minimal complexity and **high reliability**
* Ideal for **nanosatellites and maneuvering tasks**

📌 Still widely used in modern CubeSats for **fine attitude control**.

🧠 Embedded Concept of the Day – Firmware Architecture

Firmware is the **core software layer** that directly controls hardware in embedded systems.

 Key Layers

🔹 Bootloader

* Initializes the system
* Loads the main firmware

🔹 HAL (Hardware Abstraction Layer)

* SPI drivers
* I2C drivers
* UART drivers
* Abstracts hardware complexity

🔹 Application Layer

* Control loops
* State machines
* Mission logic

Why It Matters in Space

* Improves **system reliability**
* Enables easier **updates and debugging**
* Helps prevent failures caused by **radiation effects**
* Supports **redundancy and safe fallback modes**

📌 **Good firmware design = reliable space missions.**

🚀 Space Mission Update – Space Debris Tracking

Space debris has become one of the **major challenges for satellite operations**.

Current Developments

* Advanced **high-precision tracking radars**
* **AI-based collision prediction systems**
* Experimental **debris removal missions**
* Improved **orbit safety protocols**

📌 Tracking and managing debris is critical for **safe and sustainable space operations**.

